cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a novel search-based neural network model for nested and overlapping event detection in biomedical text. The model uses neural networks to model global properties for nested and overlapping structures and constructs events in a bottom-up manner. This work involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly found in the computer science sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
